Gunmen have shot a yet-to-be-identified man dead at Mofor junction in Udu Local Government Area of Delta State, DAILY POST reports. The gunmen also carted away undisclosed sum of money the victim withdrew from a Point of Sale Operator, POS, before he was attacked and killed in his car. It was learnt that the deceased was trailed to the area where the incident occurred. When contacted for comments, the Delta State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Onome Onovwakpoyeya confirmed the report in a telephone chat with our correspondent in Warri. She said, “Yes. It is true.”